 power in Trinidadian society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGayszCaribbean AreaxSocial conditions. 0aLesbiansxIdentity. 0aLesbianszCaribbean AreaxSocial conditions. 0aWomenxIdentity. 0aWomenxSexual behaviorzCaribbean Area. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aCaribbean studies, women's studies, LGBTQ, Sociology, gender, Trinidad, sexual identity, self-expression, spirituality, religion, sexuality, queer, nationalism, social class, interpersonal violence, decolonization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882140840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978821408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978821408/original  a978-3-11-076647-9  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022